  "title": "Campus Manager",
  "description": "<p>Job Description</p>\n<p>-Manage day to day operations and ensure smooth running of Tree Art campus.</p>\n<p>-Proactively engage customers and build good rapport through understanding of students and their progress development.</p>\n<p>-Engage in effective sales pitch through familiarising with Tree Art curriculum and programme.</p>\n<p>-Support management in planning and executing strategies to increase sales.</p>\n<p>-Plan, organise and communicate to customers on the various programme and campus events.</p>\n<p>-Serve as customer’s main point of contact and manage communication platforms.</p>\n<p>-Responsible for customer enquiries, student enrolment and post-sales services.</p>\n<p>-Coordinate class schedule and arrange for replacement teachers when necessary.</p>\n<p>-Monitor student attendance and follow up to arrange for makeup lesson.</p>\n<p>-Perform administrative duties including maintaining ERP, student records and tracking withdrawals.</p>\n<p>-Share expertise and provide guidance to direct report.</p>\n<p>-Motivate and work as a team in the achievement of service excellence and centre targets.</p>\n<p>-Liaise with landlord on updates.</p>\n<p>-Perform any other duties and responsibilities as assigned by the Operations Director.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Qualification:</p>\n<p>-Minimum Diploma in Business, Marketing, or a related field.</p>\n<p>-Sales experience in industries such as beauty, cosmetics, or retail services is highly desirable. -Fresh graduates with a strong sales acumen are welcome to apply.</p>\n<p>-At least 1 year of relevant experience in sales, hospitality, marketing, or education.</p>\n<p>-Proficient in Microsoft Office (Excel, Word, PowerPoint). -Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.</p>\n<p>-Meticulous, organized, and able to multitask. -Prior experience working with children is an added advantage.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Working Hours:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Monday: Off</li>\n  <li>Tuesday to Friday: 1:30 PM to 7:30 PM</li>\n  <li>Saturday and Sunday: 9:00 AM to 7:30 PM</li>\n</ul>",
